#9402
The Western Vestibule~
A small antechamber with three iron doors, each marked with a different
symbol: a spiral, a broken circle, and an eye. The doors are sealed with
mechanisms of ancient brass and bone. The floor here is inscribed with a
warning in an archaic script. The exit east returns to the entry hall.~
