#9403
The Eastern Nave~
A long hall that once served as the nave of a dark chapel. Rows of stone
pews face an altar of black glass at the far end. The pews are occupied
by skeletal figures in rotted vestments, slumped in eternal congregation.
Carved into the floor between the pews is a complex circular diagram --
a ritual seal that radiates a faint warmth, as though it still functions
after all this time. The exit west returns to the entry hall, and a door
leads north.~
