#9405
The Southern Corridor~
A long corridor running south from the entry hall. The walls here are lined
with sealed niches, each containing a mummified corpse standing upright,
wrapped in black linen and bound with silver wire. Their hollow eye sockets
seem to track your movement. The floor is treacherous -- certain flagstones
are pressure plates that trigger mechanisms in the walls. The corridor
continues south and branches east.~
