#9406
The Ossuary Alcove~
A wide alcove branching east from the southern corridor. The walls here
are entirely composed of human bones, arranged with grotesque artistry --
patterns of skulls and femurs interlocking in spiraling designs. At the
center of the far wall is a large skull set into an iron frame. Its eye
sockets glow with sickly green light. Beneath the skull is a recessed
compartment. The exit west returns to the southern corridor.~
