#9409
The Puzzle Antechamber~
A square room with four alcoves, each containing a stone statue depicting
one of the cardinal virtues corrupted: Courage shown as reckless slaughter,
Wisdom shown as manipulative scheming, Justice shown as cruel punishment,
and Mercy shown as weakness. The statues hold objects -- a blade, a tome,
scales, and an open hand respectively. The north exit is sealed with a
massive stone door covered in combination locks. An inscription above it reads
'Only the one who understands corruption may pass.' The exit south returns to
the chamber of whispers.~
