#9411
The Threshold of the Abyss~
The grand entrance to the lower crypts -- a wide landing at the top of a
massive staircase descending into absolute darkness. The architecture here
changes: instead of stone, the walls are made of some dark, slightly warm
material that is not quite rock and not quite bone. The railing along the
staircase is carved from a single piece of shadow-iron, depicting writhing
figures. The exit north returns to the gallery, and the stairs descend.~
