#9418
The Labyrinth - The False Exit~
A passage that seems to lead upward toward light -- but the light is false,
a phosphorescent patch of mold arranged to look like daylight. Beyond it,
the passage loops back on itself and deposits you back at the crossroads.
A small alcove in the wall here contains a dusty skeleton whose hands are
still pressed flat against the wall, as though it died pushing futilely
against solid stone. The exit south returns to the crossroads.~
